e most effective way of learning vocabulary in a foreign language?\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n\n```{=html}\n<form name=\"form_Q3_7\" onsubmit=\"return validate_form_Q3_7()\" method=\"post\">\n<label>\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer_Q3_7\" id=\"answer_Q3_7_1\" value=\"By first reading a word in one&#39;s native language, and then reading a translation in the target language.\"/>\nBy first reading a word in one's native language, and then reading a translation in the target language.\n</label>\n<br/>\n<label>\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer_Q3_7\" id=\"answer_Q3_7_2\" value=\"By first reading a word in the target language, and then a translation in one&#39;s native language.\"/>\nBy first reading a word in the target language, and then a translation in one's native language.\n</label>\n<br/>\n<label>\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer_Q3_7\" id=\"answer_Q3_7_3\" value=\"Beginners learn better if they are first exposed to a word in their native language and then in the target language. The opposite is true for more proficient learners.\"/>\nBeginners learn better if they are first exposed to a word in their native language and then in the target language. The opposite is true for more proficient learners.\n</label>\n<br/>\n<label>\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer_Q3_7\" id=\"answer_Q3_7_4\" value=\"It&#39;s impossible to tell as all human learners are different.\"/>\nIt's impossible to tell as all human learners are different.\n</label>\n<br/>\n<input type=\"submit\" value=\"Check answer\"/>\n<div id=\"result_Q3_7\"></div>\n</form>\n<script>function validate_form_Q3_7() {var x, text; var x = document.forms['form_Q3_7']['answer_Q3_7'].value;if (x == 'Beginners learn better if they are first exposed to a word in their native language and then in the target language. The opposite is true for more proficient learners.'){text = 'That’s right, well done!';} else {text = 'Not, quite. Remember that L1 means ‘first language’, ‘native language’ or ‘mother tongue’, whereas L2 refers to a second or foreign language.';} document.getElementById('result_Q3_7').innerHTML = text; evaluate_final_score(); return false;}function evaluate_final_score(){\n         element = document.getElementById('checkdown_final_score');\n         if(element === null){return false;} else {var element, text, res1, res2, res3, res4, res5, res6, res7;res1 = document.getElementById('result_Q3_1').innerText == 'That’s right!'; res2 = document.getElementById('result_Q3_2').innerText == 'That’s right! This filename is problematic due to the fact that it contains spaces, that it is unclear what ‘MyDocument’ and ‘final’ mean, and the use of the dot, which should only be used as part of the file extension. While mixed capitalisation will not cause any errors, it is not good filenaming practice and should therefore be avoided.'; res3 = document.getElementById('result_Q3_3').innerText == 'That’s right, well done!'; res4 = document.getElementById('result_Q3_4').innerText == 'That’s right! As suggested in the bottom-left of the screenshot, this computer is running macOS so forward slashes are used and the absolute path begins at the root which is higher up the folder hierarchy than the UzK folder.'; res5 = document.getElementById('result_Q3_5').innerText == 'That’s right!'; res6 = document.getElementById('result_Q3_6').innerText == 'That’s right!'; res7 = document.getElementById('result_Q3_7').innerText == 'That’s right, well done!';text = res1 + res2 + res3 + res4 + res5 + res6 + res7;element.innerHTML = text;\n         return false;\n         }}</script>\n```\n\n:::\n:::\n\n\nThe authors of this article have published the data and materials associated with this study on IRIS. You can find them here: <https://iris-database.org/search/?s_publicationAPAInlineReference=Terai%20et%20al.%20(2021)>\n\n[**Q3.8**]{style=\"color:green;\"} In which format are the video files associated with this publication?\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n